    PUBLIC PLAZA

    Objective

    To redesign Moor Street station, Birmingham beyond its use as a passenger transit point. The station services will be extended beyond its primary function so that the opening times can be increased to accommodate the passenger and local community needs. A key function of a newly designated space is to create an artclassroom, for beginners and semi-professionals to create and exhibit their work on the concourse or platforms of these stations. A facility to purchase the displayed work must be made possible.

    Rationale

    Given that regional stations are used by a large and diverse sector of the population, there is untapped potential in the role that stations can play to encourage activities that extend the station’s use beyond atransit point. This and most regional stations in the UK have basic facilities and ticket counters and amenities such as restaurants. Regional railway stations can be used to stimulate a larger role in educating, supporting, and influencing individuals to adopt new behaviours that are regenerative. What if we reimaginethe potential of stations to communicate and engage with the public and create momentum for positive change? This will encourage the station to be open for longer hours than the rail traffic and consequentlymake the station safer.
